<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-16581] quartz - jobs are not interrupted even if requested</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-16581</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;camel-quartz provides option &lt;tt&gt;interruptJobsOnShutdown&lt;/tt&gt;, which says the running jobs will be interrupted. &lt;br/&gt;
&lt;tt&gt;org.apache.camel.component.quartz.CamelJob&lt;/tt&gt; does not implement &lt;tt&gt;org.quartz.InterruptableJob&lt;/tt&gt; though, so when shutting down the scheduler, the running jobs in fact will &lt;b&gt;not&lt;/b&gt; be interrupted, as per implementation of &lt;tt&gt;org.quartz.core.QuartzScheduler#shutdown(boolean)&lt;/tt&gt;: &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
...
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt;(job.getJobInstance() &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;instanceof&lt;/span&gt; InterruptableJob)
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;try&lt;/span&gt; {
        ((InterruptableJob)job.getJobInstance()).interrupt();
    }
    ...
...
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The job thread stays running, and does not get any information about the scheduler shutdown.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also, if it worked, I would like to be able to configure the behavior in quartz.properties (which I supply to &lt;tt&gt;QuartzComponent&lt;/tt&gt;), as opposed to configuring it on the &lt;tt&gt;QuartzComponent&lt;/tt&gt; itself. &lt;br/&gt;
At this moment, it is needed to supply the &lt;tt&gt;interruptJobsOnShutdown&lt;/tt&gt; to the &lt;tt&gt;QuartzComponent&lt;/tt&gt;, even if my &lt;tt&gt;quartz.properties&lt;/tt&gt; already contains &lt;tt&gt;org.quartz.scheduler.interruptJobsOnShutdown=true&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
